name: adenine
description: Adenine is a nucleobase (a purine derivative).

name: deoxyribose
description: 2-deoxyribose the monosaccharide found in DNA. Query will not match RNA ribose.

name: imidazole
description: Imidazole is an organic compound with the formula C3N2H4.

name: porphin
description: The central ring in a prophyrin, for example heme.

name: porphin-like
description: prophyrin/heme connectivity regardless of bond order.

name: purine
description: A purine is a heterocyclic aromatic organic compound that consists of a pyrimidine ring fused to an imidazole ring.

name: pyrimidine
description: Pyrimidine is an aromatic heterocyclic organic compound similar to pyridine.

name: pyrrole
description: Pyrrole is a heterocyclic aromatic organic compound, a five-membered ring with the formula C4H4NH.

name: ribose
description: Will match any furanose sugar, regardless of chirality.
